:{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Plan: Add Cursor Agent Support on New Agent Interface\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe `soph/agent-refactor` branch refactored the agent system from a callback-driven model (agents call framework functions) to a dispatcher-driven model (agents are passive data providers, framework calls agent methods). PR #260 attempted to add Cursor support on the *old* interface. We need to implement Cursor support on the *new* interface.\\n\\nThe new architecture has a single `DispatchLifecycleEvent` dispatcher that routes normalized `Event` objects from any agent. Adding a new agent means:\\n1. Implement the `Agent` interface (identity + `ParseHookEvent` + transcript methods)\\n2. Implement `HookSupport` for hook installation\\n3. Implement `HookHandler` (legacy, for backward compat)\\n4. Register in `init()` — the framework auto-discovers agents\\n\\n## Branch\\n\\nCreate `robin/cursor-agent` from `soph/agent-refactor`.\\n\\n## Files to Create\\n\\n### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go` — Main agent implementation\\n\\nImplements the core `Agent` interface:\\n- **Identity:** `Name()=\\\"cursor\\\"`, `Type()=\\\"Cursor\\\"`, `Description()=\\\"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\\\"`, `DetectPresence()` checks `.cursor/` dir, `ProtectedDirs()=[\\\".cursor\\\"]`\\n- **Event Mapping:**\\n  - `HookNames()` → `[\\\"session-start\\\", \\\"session-end\\\", \\\"before-submit-prompt\\\", \\\"stop\\\", \\\"pre-task\\\", \\\"post-task\\\", \\\"post-todo\\\"]`\\n  - `ParseHookEvent()` maps hooks to lifecycle events (see mapping table below)\\n- **Transcript Storage:** `ReadTranscript`, `ChunkTranscript`, `ReassembleTranscript` — JSONL format (same as Claude Code, delegate to `agent.ChunkJSONL`/`agent.ReassembleJSONL`)\\n- **Legacy methods:** `ParseHookInput`, `GetSessionID`, `GetSessionDir`, `ResolveSessionFile`, `ReadSession`, `WriteSession`, `FormatResumeCommand`, `GetHookConfigPath`, `SupportsHooks`\\n\\nPattern to follow: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/claude.go`\\n\\n### 2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle.go` — Event parsing\\n\\nCore `ParseHookEvent` implementation with private parse methods:\\n- `parseSessionStart(stdin)` → `Event{Type: SessionStart, SessionID, SessionRef}`\\n- `parseTurnStart(stdin)` → `Event{Type: TurnStart, SessionID, SessionRef, Prompt}`\\n- `parseTurnEnd(stdin)` → `Event{Type: TurnEnd, SessionID, SessionRef}`\\n- `parseSessionEnd(stdin)` → `Event{Type: SessionEnd, SessionID, SessionRef}`\\n- `parseSubagentStart(stdin)` → `Event{Type: SubagentStart, SessionID, SessionRef, ToolUseID, ToolInput}`\\n- `parseSubagentEnd(stdin)` → `Event{Type: SubagentEnd, SessionID, SessionRef, ToolUseID, SubagentID, ToolInput}`\\n- `post-todo` → `nil, nil` (no lifecycle action, handled specially like Claude)\\n\\nAlso implement `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface:\\n- `GetTranscriptPosition(path)` — line count (JSONL)\\n- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(path, startOffset)` — parse JSONL lines, extract Write/Edit tools\\n- `ExtractPrompts(sessionRef, fromOffset)` — extract user messages\\n- `ExtractSummary(sessionRef)` — last assistant text\\n\\n**Key insight:** Cursor uses the same JSONL transcript format as Claude Code (confirmed by PR #260 and Cursor docs). We can reuse Claude's transcript parsing utilities from the `transcript` package.\\n\\nPattern to follow: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go`\\n\\n### 3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/hooks.go` — Hook installation\\n\\nImplements `HookSupport` and `HookHandler` interfaces:\\n- `InstallHooks(localDev, force)` — writes `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `UninstallHooks()` — removes Entire entries from `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `AreHooksInstalled()` — checks for Entire hooks\\n- `GetSupportedHooks()` — returns supported hook types\\n- `GetHookNames()` — returns hook verb list (delegates to `HookNames()`)\\n\\n**Cursor hooks.json format:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"sessionStart\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor session-start\\\"}],\\n    \\\"sessionEnd\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor session-end\\\"}],\\n    \\\"beforeSubmitPrompt\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor before-submit-prompt\\\"}],\\n    \\\"stop\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor stop\\\"}],\\n    \\\"preToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor pre-task\\\", \\\"matcher\\\": \\\"Task\\\"}],\\n    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [\\n      {\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor post-task\\\", \\\"matcher\\\": \\\"Task\\\"},\\n      {\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor post-todo\\\", \\\"matcher\\\": \\\"TodoWrite\\\"}\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNote: Cursor's preToolUse/postToolUse support `matcher` field for filtering by tool name (similar to Claude's structure). The `matcher` field is optional.\\n\\nPattern to follow: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/hooks.go`\\n\\n### 4. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/types.go` — Type definitions\\n\\nCursor-specific types:\\n- `CursorHooksFile` — root `.cursor/hooks.json` structure\\n- `CursorHooks` — hook arrays (camelCase keys: `sessionStart`, `sessionEnd`, `beforeSubmitPrompt`, `stop`, `preToolUse`, `postToolUse`)\\n- `CursorHookEntry` — `{command, matcher?}`\\n- stdin payload structs: `sessionInfoRaw`, `userPromptSubmitRaw`, `taskHookInputRaw`, `postToolHookInputRaw`\\n\\nCursor payloads include both `session_id` and `conversation_id` (fallback). Use `session_id` if present, fall back to `conversation_id`.\\n\\nPattern to follow: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/types.go`\\n\\n### 5. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/hooks_test.go` — Hook installation tests\\n\\nTests:\\n- `TestInstallHooks_FreshInstall` — verify hooks.json created with all hooks\\n- `TestInstallHooks_Idempotent` — verify no double-install\\n- `TestAreHooksInstalled_NotInstalled`\\n- `TestAreHooksInstalled_AfterInstall`\\n- `TestUninstallHooks`\\n- `TestInstallHooks_ForceReinstall`\\n- `TestInstallHooks_PreservesExistingHooks`\\n\\n### 6. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle_test.go` — Event parsing tests\\n\\nTests:\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SessionStart`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_TurnStart`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_TurnEnd`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SessionEnd`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SubagentStart`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SubagentEnd`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_PostTodo_ReturnsNil`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_UnknownHook_ReturnsNil`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput_ReturnsError`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_ConversationIDFallback`\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n### 7. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go` — Add Cursor constants\\n\\nAdd:\\n```go\\nAgentNameCursor AgentName = \\\"cursor\\\"\\nAgentTypeCursor AgentType = \\\"Cursor\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### 8. `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` — Import cursor package\\n\\nAdd blank import `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor\\\"` to trigger `init()` registration.\\n\\n### 9. `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` — Add Cursor post-todo handling\\n\\nThe lifecycle dispatcher handles all standard events. But `post-todo` is a special case (like Claude Code's). Add Cursor's `post-todo` handling alongside Claude's in `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging`:\\n\\n```go\\n} else if agentName == agent.AgentNameCursor && hookName == cursor.HookNamePostTodo {\\n    hookErr = handleCursorPostTodo(ag, cmd.InOrStdin())\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAlso update `getHookType()` to recognize Cursor's task-related hooks.\\n\\n### 10. `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cursor_handlers.go` (NEW) — Cursor post-todo handler\\n\\nSingle function `handleCursorPostTodo(ag, stdin)` that:\\n1. Parses PostToolUse input from stdin\\n2. Checks for active pre-task file\\n3. Delegates to the existing `runPostTodoLogic()` function from the lifecycle dispatcher\\n\\nActually, looking at the refactor branch more carefully — the lifecycle dispatcher already handles all events generically. The only special case is `post-todo` which returns `nil` from `ParseHookEvent`. We need a small handler file for this.\\n\\n### 11. `cmd/entire/cli/setup.go` — Minor adjustments\\n\\nThe setup flow already works generically via the `agent.Get()` / `HookSupport` interface. The only change needed is the \\\"Preview\\\" label for Cursor (like Gemini).\\n\\n## Hook Name → Event Mapping\\n\\n| Cursor Hook Name | Event Type | Notes |\\n|------------------|------------|-------|\\n| `session-start` | `SessionStart` | Same as Claude |\\n| `before-submit-prompt` | `TurnStart` | Cursor's name for user-prompt-submit |\\n| `stop` | `TurnEnd` | Same as Claude |\\n| `session-end` | `SessionEnd` | Same as Claude |\\n| `pre-task` | `SubagentStart` | Maps from preToolUse[Task] |\\n| `post-task` | `SubagentEnd` | Maps from postToolUse[Task] |\\n| `post-todo` | `nil` | Incremental checkpoint, handled directly |\\n\\n## Key Design Decisions\\n\\n1. **JSONL transcript format**: Cursor uses the same JSONL format as Claude Code. Reuse the `transcript` package utilities for parsing.\\n\\n2. **No TranscriptPreparer**: Cursor doesn't need the sentinel-polling that Claude Code uses. The transcript is synchronously written before hooks fire.\\n\\n3. **conversation_id fallback**: Cursor payloads may send `conversation_id` instead of `session_id`. Parse both, prefer `session_id`.\\n\\n4. **Matcher support in hooks.json**: Cursor's hooks.json supports an optional `matcher` field on hook entries (similar to Claude's per-tool filtering). Use this for pre-task (Task matcher) and post-todo (TodoWrite matcher).\\n\\n5. **No settings merge**: Unlike PR #260's `.cursor/entire.json` approach, we use `.entire/settings.json` as the single source of truth. Cursor doesn't need separate settings.\\n\\n## Reusable Code\\n\\n- `agent.ChunkJSONL()` / `agent.ReassembleJSONL()` from `cmd/entire/cli/agent/chunking.go`\\n- `transcript.ParseFromBytes()`, `transcript.ParseFromFileAtLine()` from `cmd/entire/cli/transcript/`\\n- `transcript.ExtractUserContent()` for prompt extraction\\n- `claudecode.ExtractModifiedFiles()` logic pattern (but Cursor may have different tool names)\\n- Generic `readAndParse[T]()` pattern from Claude/Gemini lifecycle.go\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint` — ensure code passes formatting and linting\\n2. `mise run test` — unit tests pass\\n3. `mise run test:integration` — integration tests pass\\n4. `mise run test:ci` — full CI suite\\n5. Manual verification:\\n   - `go build ./cmd/entire/` compiles\\n   - `go run ./cmd/entire/ enable --agent cursor` in a test repo creates `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n   - `go run ./cmd/entire/ disable` removes hooks from `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n   - Hook commands exist: `go run ./cmd/entire/ hooks cursor --help` shows all hook verbs\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/robin/.REDACTED.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"30faaae3-412d-4a00-9ef6-164ce1ec1b42\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-17T16:24:28.799Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Plan: Add Cursor Agent Support on New Agent Interface\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe `soph/agent-refactor` branch refactored the agent system from a callback-driven model (agents call framework functions) to a dispatcher-driven model (agents are passive data providers, framework calls agent methods). PR #260 attempted to add Cursor support on the *old* interface. We need to implement Cursor support on the *new* interface.\\n\\nThe new architecture has a single `DispatchLifecycleEvent` dispatcher that routes normalized `Event` objects from any agent. Adding a new agent means:\\n1. Implement the `Agent` interface (identity + `ParseHookEvent` + transcript methods)\\n2. Implement `HookSupport` for hook installation\\n3. Implement `HookHandler` (legacy, for backward compat)\\n4. Register in `init()` — the framework auto-discovers agents\\n\\n## Branch\\n\\nCreate `robin/cursor-agent` from `soph/agent-refactor`.\\n\\n## Files to Create\\n\\n### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go` — Main 