ile naming\\n- `DetectAgentTypeFromContent(content)` -- checks if content is Gemini JSON format\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/session.go` -- AgentSession\\n\\n`AgentSession` struct: `SessionID`, `AgentName`, `RepoPath`, `SessionRef`, `StartTime`, `NativeData` (raw bytes in agent's native format), `ModifiedFiles`, `NewFiles`, `DeletedFiles`, `Entries`\\n\\nSessions are **not interoperable** between agents. Each agent reads/writes its own format.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. Claude Code Agent (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/`)\\n\\nThis is the reference implementation. Files:\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/claude.go` -- Main Implementation\\n\\n- Self-registers in `init()`: `agent.Register(agent.AgentNameClaudeCode, NewClaudeCodeAgent)`\\n- Struct: `ClaudeCodeAgent struct{}` (empty, stateless)\\n- `DetectPresence()` checks for `.claude/` directory at repo root\\n- `GetSessionDir()` returns `~/.claude/projects/<sanitized-path>/`\\n- `ResolveSessionFile()` returns `<dir>/<id>.jsonl`\\n- Transcript format: **JSONL** (one JSON object per line)\\n- `GetTranscriptPosition()` counts lines (lightweight, no JSON parse)\\n- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset()` parses JSONL from offset, extracts files from Write/Edit tools\\n- `ChunkTranscript()` / `ReassembleTranscript()` delegate to `agent.ChunkJSONL` / `agent.ReassembleJSONL`\\n- `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()` and `CalculateTotalTokenUsage()` include subagent transcripts\\n- `FormatResumeCommand()` returns `\\\"claude -r \\\" + sessionID`\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/types.go` -- Claude-Specific Types\\n\\n- `ClaudeSettings`, `ClaudeHooks`, `ClaudeHookMatcher`, `ClaudeHookEntry` -- settings.json structure\\n- `sessionInfoRaw`, `userPromptSubmitRaw`, `taskHookInputRaw`, `postToolHookInputRaw` -- raw JSON from hooks\\n- File modification tool names: `Write`, `Edit`, `NotebookEdit`, `mcp__acp__Write`, `mcp__acp__Edit`\\n- `messageUsage` / `messageWithUsage` -- for token calculation\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/hooks.go` -- Hook Installation\\n\\n- Implements `HookSupport` and `HookHandler` interfaces\\n- `GetHookNames()` returns 7 hooks: `session-start`, `session-end`, `stop`, `user-prompt-submit`, `pre-task`, `post-task`, `post-todo`\\n- `InstallHooks()` reads/modifies `.claude/settings.json` preserving unknown fields\\n- Also adds `permissions.deny` rule to block Claude from reading metadata\\n- Commands use form: `\\\"entire hooks claude-code <verb>\\\"` (or `\\\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/...\\\"` for localDev)\\n- `entireHookPrefixes` used to identify Entire hooks\\n- `UninstallHooks()` removes only Entire hooks, preserving user hooks\\n- `AreHooksInstalled()` checks for known command patterns\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/transcript.go` -- Transcript Parsing\\n\\n- `TranscriptLine` is an alias for `transcript.Line`\\n- `ExtractModifiedFiles()` -- scans assistant messages for tool_use blocks with file modification tools\\n- `ExtractLastUserPrompt()` -- handles both string and array content formats\\n- `TruncateAtUUID()` -- returns lines up to UUID\\n- `FindCheckpointUUID()` -- finds tool_result for a given tool_use_id\\n- `CalculateTokenUsage()` -- deduplicates by message.id (handles streaming duplicates)\\n- `ExtractSpawnedAgentIDs()` -- finds \\\"agentId: <id>\\\" in Task tool results\\n- `CalculateTotalTokenUsage()` / `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()` -- include subagent data\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` -- Lifecycle Event Parsing\\n\\n- Compile-time assertions: implements `TranscriptAnalyzer`, `TranscriptPreparer`, `TokenCalculator`, `SubagentAwareExtractor`\\n- `HookNames()` delegates to `GetHookNames()`\\n- `ParseHookEvent()` -- the key switch statement mapping hook names to event types:\\n  - `session-start` -> `SessionStart`\\n  - `user-prompt-submit`