oreModel`, `AfterModel`, `BeforeToolSelection`, `BeforeTool`, `AfterTool`, `PreCompress`, `Notification`\\n- `sessionInfoRaw` has extra fields: `Cwd`, `HookEventName`, `Source`, `Reason`\\n- `geminiMessageTokens` with `Input`, `Output`, `Cached`, `Thoughts`, `Tool`, `Total`\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/hooks.go` -- Hook Installation\\n\\n- 11 hook names (more than Claude's 7): `session-start`, `session-end`, `before-agent`, `after-agent`, `before-model`, `after-model`, `before-tool-selection`, `before-tool`, `after-tool`, `pre-compress`, `notification`\\n- `InstallHooks()` sets `hooksConfig.enabled = true` (Gemini requires this)\\n- Installs 12 hooks total (session-end installs two: exit + logout matchers)\\n- Uses `entireHookPrefixes` with `\\\"entire \\\"` and `\\\"go run ${GEMINI_PROJECT_DIR}/...\\\"`\\n- Has idempotency check (returns 0 if same hooks already installed)\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle.go` -- Lifecycle Event Parsing\\n\\n- Implements `TranscriptAnalyzer`, `TokenCalculator`\\n- Does NOT implement `TranscriptPreparer` or `SubagentAwareExtractor`\\n- `ParseHookEvent()` mappings:\\n  - `session-start` -> `SessionStart`\\n  - `before-agent` -> `TurnStart` (Gemini's equivalent of UserPromptSubmit)\\n  - `after-agent` -> `TurnEnd` (Gemini's equivalent of Stop)\\n  - `session-end` -> `SessionEnd`\\n  - `pre-compress` -> `Compaction` (unique to Gemini)\\n  - `before-tool`, `after-tool`, `before-model`, `after-model`, `before-tool-selection`, `notification` -> `nil` (no lifecycle action)\\n- `readAndParse[T]()` -- same generic pattern as Claude\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/transcript.go` -- Transcript Parsing\\n\\n- `GeminiTranscript` struct with `Messages []GeminiMessage`\\n- `GeminiMessage` has custom `UnmarshalJSON` to handle both string and array content\\n- `GeminiToolCall` with `Args map[string]interface{}`\\n- File path extraction checks `file_path`, `path`, `filename` args\\n- `SliceFromMessage()` -- equivalent of `transcript.SliceFromLine` but by message index\\n- `CalculateTokenUsage()` / `CalculateTokenUsageFromFile()` -- processes `tokens` object per message\\n\\nThe \\\"(Preview)\\\" label for Gemini appears in `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/setup.go` at line 620-629:\\n```go\\nif agentName == agent.AgentNameGemini {\\n    msg += \\\" (Preview)\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. Hook System\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` -- Hook Command Tree\\n\\n- Creates `entire hooks` command (hidden, internal)\\n- Adds `entire hooks git` subcommand for strategy-level git hooks\\n- **Dynamically adds agent subcommands**: iterates `agent.List()`, casts to `HookHandler`, calls `newAgentHooksCmd()`\\n- Imports agents to ensure registration: `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode\\\"` and `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli\\\"`\\n\\n**For a new Cursor agent, you would add:**\\n```go\\n_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor\\\"\\n```\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` -- Hook Dispatch\\n\\n- `currentHookAgentName` -- tracks which agent is running the current hook\\n- `GetCurrentHookAgent()` -- returns agent from hook context\\n- `newAgentHooksCmd()` -- creates `entire hooks <agentName>` command with logging setup\\n- `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging()` -- creates individual verb commands (e.g., `entire hooks claude-code stop`)\\n- **Critical dispatch logic:**\\n  1. Checks if in git repo and Entire is enabled (silent skip if not)\\n  2. Gets agent via `agent.Get(agentName)`\\n  3. Calls `ag.ParseHookEvent(hookName, cmd.InOrStdin())` to get normalized Event\\n  4. If event is non-nil: calls `DispatchLifecycleEvent(ag, event)` (generic dispatcher)\\n  5. Special case: Claude's `post-todo` is handled directly via `handleClaudeCodePostTodo()`\\n  6. All