e starting from line offset, returns `([]Line, totalLines, error)`\\n- `SliceFromLine(content, startLine)` -- returns byte content starting from line offset\\n- `ExtractUserContent(message)` -- extracts text from user messages (handles string and array formats), strips IDE context tags\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. Setup Flow (`cmd/entire/cli/setup.go`)\\n\\n#### `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/setup.go` -- Enable/Disable Commands\\n\\n**`entire enable` command** supports:\\n- `--agent <name>` -- non-interactive mode for specific agent\\n- `--strategy <name>` -- manual-commit or auto-commit\\n- `--local-dev` -- use `go run` instead of binary\\n- `--force` / `-f` -- force reinstall hooks\\n- `--skip-push-sessions` -- disable session log pushing\\n- `--telemetry` -- enable/disable analytics\\n\\n**Enable flow:**\\n1. Check git repository\\n2. Detect/select agent\\n3. Install agent hooks (`ag.(HookSupport).InstallHooks()`)\\n4. Create `.entire/` directory with `.gitignore`\\n5. Save settings (strategy, enabled flag, etc.)\\n6. Install git hooks (`strategy.InstallGitHook()`)\\n7. Prompt telemetry consent (interactive mode)\\n8. Call `strat.EnsureSetup()`\\n\\n**`setupAgentHooksNonInteractive()`** is the key function for `--agent` mode:\\n- Casts to `HookSupport`, installs hooks\\n- Appends \\\"(Preview)\\\" suffix for Gemini agent\\n- Saves settings, installs git hooks, calls strategy setup\\n\\n**`isFullyEnabled()`** checks: settings exist + enabled, any agent hooks installed, git hooks installed, `.entire/` dir exists.\\n\\n**`entire disable --uninstall`** removes: agent hooks (all registered), git hooks, session states, `.entire/` directory, shadow branches.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Key Patterns for Implementing a Cursor Agent\\n\\n1. **Create package** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/` with files following the same structure:\\n   - `cursor.go` -- main implementation with `init()` self-registration\\n   - `types.go` -- Cursor-specific types (settings structure, hook input f